    <h1>Pokemon Database</h1>
    <p>I have chosen the Pokemon API as my data source for this project. This data source contains an overwhelming amount of data. As such, I've decided to include the following:</p>
    <h3>Tables:<h3>
    <p>Pokemon</p>
    <p>Types</p>
    <p>Abilities</p>
    <p>This will require two join tables:</p>
    <p>PokemonTypes</p>
    <p>PokemonAbilities</p>
    <p>Tables will have the following columns:</p>
    <p>Pokemon:</p>
    <p>name</p>
    <p>height</p>
    <p>weight</p>
    <p>pokemon_id</p>
    <p>order</p>
    <p>Types:</p>
    <p>name</p>
    <p>type_id</p>
    <p>generation</p>
    <p>Abilities:</p>
    <p>name</p>
    <p>generation</p>
    <p>ability_id</p>

    <p>These tables will contain Foreign Keys for the appropriate Join tables as well as ID Primary Keys. These will be generated by Rails.</p></div>
